# regression_data_smoke.numos — Phase 7C: type a small dataset into RegressionApp.
#
# Unlike regression_smoke.numos (which only opens the app on its default empty "Data"
# tab), this script proves RegressionApp is INTERACTABLE *with real numeric entry*: it
# types the three points {(1,2),(2,4),(3,6)} into the X/Y table and switches to the
# computed "Equation" tab, which runs the least-squares RegressionEngine over actual
# data — a code path the open-only smoke never reaches. The points lie exactly on
# y = 2x, so the linear fit is slope 2, intercept 0, R^2 = 1.
#
# Data-entry flow (the table starts with exactly ONE row, _numRows=1, two columns X|Y;
# RegressionApp.cpp:218-219, 707-839):
#   * On the Data tab, pressing a digit in nav mode starts an edit and re-processes the
#     digit (RegressionApp.cpp:831-836 -> startEdit() + handleKeyData). ENTER commits the
#     value via finishEdit() (atof of the buffer) and returns to nav mode
#     (RegressionApp.cpp:776-779, 422-438).
#   * RIGHT/LEFT move between the X (col 0) and Y (col 1) columns; on the Data tab they are
#     column nav, NOT a tab switch (RegressionApp.cpp:801-812).
#   * AC (nav mode) appends a fresh row (x=0, y=0, ++_numRows); DOWN moves the focus to it
#     (RegressionApp.cpp:822-830, 795-800). So the per-row pattern is: LEFT (back to X col),
#     AC (new row), DOWN (move to it), type X, RIGHT, type Y.
#   * Digits use the order-independent keyCodeDigitValue() helper (RegressionApp.cpp:744,833;
#     KeyCodes.h) — RegressionApp has NO digit-range bug (it was fixed repo-wide in Phase 6E).
#   * Note on display: startEdit() pre-fills the editor with the cell's current value when the
#     row already holds data (RegressionApp.cpp:409-414), so a Y-column edit briefly shows a
#     leading "0" (e.g. ">02_"); atof absorbs it harmlessly (atof("02")==2), so the COMMITTED
#     values are exactly {(1,2),(2,4),(3,6)}. After finishEdit()->refreshTable() each cell is
#     reformatted normally.
#   * GRAPH cycles Data -> Equation -> Graph; on the Data tab it is the ONLY key that leaves
#     the Data tab (LEFT/RIGHT are column nav). switchTab(EQUATION) calls recompute() +
#     updateEquationDisplay() over the typed points (RegressionApp.cpp:723-727, 330-339,
#     462-463). Pure <cmath> RegressionEngine: no Giac/CAS, no PSRAM, no LittleFS. Fully
#     deterministic.
#
# RegressionApp has NO update() method and no timer-driven cursor blink, so the only volatile
# region is the StatusBar clock (HH:MM). This phase makes NO golden claim; the screenshot is a
# CANDIDATE for human review only (a clock mask is added by the human at promotion time,
# rect 4,6,37,13).
#
# Timing notes (deterministic, step-ms 16):
#   * 200 frames -> splash done, in launcher.
#   * 60 frames  -> Regression screen load + fade settles after open_app.
#   * one frame per key command (1 command/frame).
#   * 120 frames -> Data->Equation tab switch + recompute() settles.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/regression_data_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/regression_data_smoke.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "regression_data_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

# Open Regression (emulator launchApp id 6 — same id as the launcher's Regression card).
open_app Regression
wait 60
assert_app Regression

# Row 0: X=1 (col 0), move to Y col, Y=2.
key 1
key enter
key right
key 2
key enter

# Row 1: back to X col, append a row, move down to it, X=2, Y=4.
key left
key ac
key down
key 2
key enter
key right
key 4
key enter

# Row 2: back to X col, append a row, move down to it, X=3, Y=6.
key left
key ac
key down
key 3
key enter
key right
key 6
key enter

# Switch Data -> Equation: GRAPH is the only key that leaves the Data tab, and it triggers
# recompute() + updateEquationDisplay() over the typed points {(1,2),(2,4),(3,6)} -> y = 2x.
key graph
wait 120

# Screenshot FIRST so the artifact exists even if a later assertion fails.
screenshot out/regression_data_smoke.ppm
log "regression_data_smoke: screenshot captured (Equation tab, linear fit y=2x over {(1,2),(2,4),(3,6)})"

# Still the Regression app after the in-app tab switch (tab switch does not change g_mode).
assert_app Regression
log "regression_data_smoke: assertion passed (Regression active)"
